import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    occupations = data['job'].unique()
    colors = plt.cm.get_cmap('tab20', len(occupations))
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    
    for idx, occupation in enumerate(occupations):
        occupation_data = data[data['job'] == occupation]
        men_data = occupation_data[occupation_data['sex'] == 'men']
        women_data = occupation_data[occupation_data['sex'] == 'women']
        
        plt.plot(men_data['year'], men_data['perc'], label=f'{occupation} - Men', color=colors(idx))
        plt.plot(women_data['year'], women_data['perc'], label=f'{occupation} - Women', linestyle='--', color=colors(idx))
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage')
    plt.title('What is the trend of gender distribution in different occupations over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1), title='Occupations')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_occupations = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
    top_occupations.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple', 'brown', 'pink', 'gray', 'olive', 'cyan'])
    plt.title('What are the top 10 occupations with the highest number of individuals in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Occupation')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Individuals')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Number of Individuals'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_men = data[data['sex'] == 'men']
    data_women = data[data['sex'] == 'women']

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data_men['perc'], data_women['perc']], labels=['Men', 'Women'])
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of percentage of individuals in different occupations for each gender?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percentage')
    ax.legend(['Men', 'Women'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='year', hue='job', multiple='stack', palette='tab20', bins=15)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count of individuals in different occupations for each year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Individuals')
    plt.legend(title='Occupations', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_occupations = data.nlargest(5, 'perc')
    gender_distribution = top_occupations.groupby(['job', 'sex'])['count'].sum().unstack()
    gender_distribution.plot(kind='pie', subplots=True, legend=True, autopct='%.2f%%', figsize=(15, 8))
    plt.title("What is the gender distribution in the top 5 occupations with the highest percentage of individuals?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
